observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the management agreed to:
a. Direct the General Services Officer with the Inventory Committee to conduct complete physical count and classify properly the accounts presented in the RPCPPE;
b. Direct the concerned department to complete the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts intended to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition, and accountability;
c. Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjusting entries in order to reconcile the balances per financial statements against the RPCPPE prepared by the General Services Office and make full disclosures of the related information in the Notes to the Financial Statements;
d. Constantly review and monitor the system-generated depreciation schedule for the PPE and evaluate the correctness of the data using the underlying provisions and basis of computation provided in IPSAS 17; and
e. Exert effort to provide a manual computation on the depreciation charges and make necessary adjusting entries to correct the amount of depreciation of the properties.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the following:
a. Municipal General Services Officer:
1. Conduct complete physical count and classify properly the accounts presented in the RPCPPE;
2. Maintain proper and complete records of the PPEs, particularly the stock cards and property cards in compliance with the applicable rules and regulations;
3. Complete the disposal procedures of the remaining unserviceable properties in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency; and
4. Follow the procedures set forth under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 for the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts of the LGU to establish the accountability, condition, and existence of PPEs.

We recommended the following:
The Acting Municipal General Services Officer shall maintain updated and properly accomplished property cards for property accountabilities;
The Accounting Department shall establish and maintain updated PPELCs;

The Local Chief Executive shall create an Inventory Committee to conduct a complete actual physical count of PPE. The result of the physical count shall be reported in RPCPPE and are promptly reconciled with accountabilities recorded in the books of accounts and the property cards and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor.
